	<text>
		<body>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/11608943/gabersee.html">Gabersee</placeName> Blok N number 13</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_lea_adler">Adler Lea</persName>, seventeen years old. Finished two classes of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">gymnasium</term>. Born in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/687449/zboriv.html">Zboriv</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>. In the first period of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-632" type="subject">occupation</term> they carried out a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-346" type="subject">pogrom</term>. After the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-346" type="subject">pogrom</term>, there was an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">aktion</term>. During the action, they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">decimated</term> almost all the Jews of the city. From
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">cold and hunger</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-862" type="subject">died en masse</term>. During the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-551" type="subject">liquidation of the ghetto</term>, I, together with my
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">parents</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. Not being eighteen years old, I had to
				leave and part with my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">parents</term>. I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">relatives</term>, to whom my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">parents</term> sent me. Coming out of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunker</term>, I discovered that my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">parents</term>, poor things, were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">not alive</term>. I left the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunker</term> on <date when="1944-08-19">August 19,
					1944</date>.</p>

			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_lea_adler">Adler Lea</persName></p>

